<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="525" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1624,2009]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1624,1649]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Epandrium lobe acuminate at apex (
<figureCitation box="[690,849,1624,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Figs 
<number box="[748,849,1624,1649]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="116117.0">116, 117</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallus narrow, much longer than the hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[159,258,1660,1685]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Fig. 
<number box="[213,258,1661,1685]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="121.0">121</number>
</figureCitation>
); subepandrial sclerite as wide as long (
<figureCitation box="[716,816,1660,1685]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Fig. 
<number box="[770,816,1661,1685]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="120.0">120</number>
</figureCitation>
); bacilliform sclerite shorter than subepandrial sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[159,258,1696,1721]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,258,1697,1721]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="120.0">120</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1624,2009]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1436,151,824]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,416,1732,1757]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[435,536,1732,1757]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Fig. 
<number box="[491,536,1733,1757]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="114.0">114</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[559,623,1732,1757]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">Head</emphasis>
: Face slightly divergent toward the proboscis, dark brown, with gray pruinescence visible in ventral view, about 
<date box="[643,678,1769,1793]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
<number box="[643,657,1769,1793]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="4.0">4</number>
X
</date>
longer than lower width. Ocellar tubercle protrubeant, dark brown with gray pruinescence; ocelli brown. Antenna brown to black bristles; postpedicel about 
<number box="[1153,1186,1804,1829]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X longer than pedicel; stylus about 
<number box="[295,328,1840,1865]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X longer than postpedicel. Proboscis yellow shorter than head height. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1127,1216,1840,1865]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">Thorax</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,196,1877,1901]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="114.0">114</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs yellow, except for hind femur and tibia with apical black ring and all tarsomeres 
<number box="[1192,1234,1876,1901]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
brown; hind tibia with anterodorsal and posterodorsal rows of longer bristles. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[890,955,1912,1937]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[979,1081,1912,1937]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Fig. 
<number box="[1039,1081,1912,1937]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="115.0">115</number>
</figureCitation>
) hyaline, brown pterostigma, conspicuous, about 
<number box="[374,409,1949,1973]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="2.3">2.3</number>
X longer than wide. Halter yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,927,1948,1973]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">Abdomen</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1200,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">
Fig. 
<number box="[1155,1200,1949,1973]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="114.0">114</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergite 
<number box="[1300,1314,1949,1973]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two subtriangular plates; sternite 
<number box="[524,538,1985,2009]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two trapezoidal plates. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[924,1055,1984,2009]" pageId="23" pageNumber="525">Terminalia</emphasis>
: Anterior cercus with proclinate dorsal projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[526,684,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Figs 
<number box="[584,684,151,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="116117.0">116, 117</number>
</figureCitation>
), with posterior margin slightly concave in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1423,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[1378,1423,152,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="118.0">118</number>
</figureCitation>
); descendant plate subrectangular in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[726,824,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[779,824,188,212]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="119.0">119</number>
</figureCitation>
). Posterior cercus with acuminate apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,318,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Figs 
<number box="[217,318,223,248]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="116117.0">116, 117</number>
</figureCitation>
); with dorsal projections, a subbasal pointed and a submedian subtriangular (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1296,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[1251,1296,224,248]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="118.0">118</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct bacilliform lateral view and covering inner surface of the posterior cercus in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1307,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[1262,1307,260,284]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="117.0">117</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrial ventral lobe with acuminate apex (
<figureCitation box="[537,692,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Figs 
<number box="[593,692,295,320]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="116117.0">116, 117</number>
</figureCitation>
), with spiniform bristles mesially and longer bristles apically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,196,332,356]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="117.0">117</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium longer than wide, with concave apex (
<figureCitation box="[812,912,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[867,912,332,356]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="122.0">122</number>
</figureCitation>
), without long bristles. Phallus narrow, much longer than the hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[488,588,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[543,588,368,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="121.0">121</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite as wide as long, U-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1184,1285,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[1239,1285,368,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="120.0">120</number>
</figureCitation>
). Bacilliform sclerite without folds and shorter than subepandrial sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[823,920,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 114 – 122" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1804,1827]" captionTargetBox="[169,1423,200,1776]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1424,193,1783]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 114 – 122. Opeatocerata megalophallus sp. nov., holotype ♂. 114. habitus, lateral view; 115. wing; 116. abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 117. terminalia, lateral view; 118. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 119. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypoproct, posterior view; 120. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 121. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 122. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252534/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="527">
Fig. 
<number box="[874,920,404,428]" pageId="25" pageNumber="527" value="120.0">120</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
